cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper proposes the use of a deep neural network for precipitation nowcasting, which involves image processing and prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of a learned prior distribution, which suggests a probabilistic approach and makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the use of a stochastic variational frame predictor and the comparison to a standard LSTM network suggest a focus on optimization and training, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the structural similarity index, which is a measure of image quality, indicating a potential focus on signal processing and image analysis, making cs.SD (Sound and Image Processing) a possible sub-category.
